						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying near a well about two furlongs from the Vināyaka temple.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to record a gift of land, after purchase, to Narasiṁhadēva-ayya on the occasion of a <hi rend="bold">solar eclipse.</hi> The details are all lost. <hi rend="bold">Malaya-daṇṇāyaka</hi> is stated to have been governing <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya.</hi> The record refers to Upūru. </p>						

						</summary>
